# .db-design-ignore — example ignore file for the postgres-schema-audit skill
#
# Format: <pattern>    # <required justification comment>
#
# Patterns can be:
#   - schema.table              — suppress all findings on a table
#   - schema.table.column       — suppress all findings on a column
#   - schema.function_name      — suppress all findings on a function
#   - schema.*:<code>           — suppress a specific subtype code in a schema
#   - public.*:H5               — suppress "missing-table-comment" in public
#   - DB-042                    — suppress a specific finding ID from a prior run
#
# Every entry MUST have a justification comment. Unjustified entries are
# reported as "unjustified ignore" warnings during Phase 6.
#
# Patterns matching zero findings in the current run are reported as
# "stale ignore" warnings — remove them to keep the file tidy.

# === Framework / managed conventions ===
# Supabase internal schemas (already excluded globally, listed here for clarity)
auth.*                              # managed by Supabase
storage.*                           # managed by Supabase

# === Tables intentionally without RLS ===
# Reference-data tables that are world-readable by design.
public.countries                    # public reference data — RLS not needed
public.currencies                   # public reference data
public.timezones                    # public reference data

# === Tables intentionally using text keys ===
# Some tables use human-readable keys by design (slugs, codes).
public.plans                        # plan codes are the primary key by design
public.feature_flags                # flag names are the primary key by design

# === Columns intentionally nullable ===
# Columns that are semantically optional and should not be NOT NULL.
operations.tasks.completed_at       # NULL means "not yet complete" — correct
operations.contracts.terminated_at  # NULL means "still active" — correct
operations.users.last_login_at      # NULL means "never logged in" — correct

# === Suppress specific subtype codes ===
# The whole schema is legacy and we're not making design improvements to it.
legacy.*:*                          # legacy schema on sunset track — Q4 2026 decommission

# Don't nag about H5 (missing-table-comment) in public — we use schema.org comments elsewhere.
public.*:H5                         # comments live in schema.org docs, not in pg_catalog

# === Intentionally denormalised JSONB ===
# JSONB columns whose shape is deliberately flexible.
analytics.events.properties         # freeform event properties — must stay JSONB
operations.audit_log.changeset      # polymorphic diff payload

# === Functions with locked search_path intentionally ===
# These are SECURITY INVOKER so search_path doesn't need locking; the audit's
# F2 check is a false positive here.
public.pgrst_watch                  # PostgREST watchdog — SECURITY INVOKER
public.graphql_introspection        # pg_graphql hook — SECURITY INVOKER

# === Specific finding IDs suppressed from a prior run ===
# Use sparingly. Reference a specific audit report.
DB-042                              # reviewed 11/04/2026 — accepted design decision
DB-067                              # reviewed 11/04/2026 — scheduled for Q3 migration
